	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64500503"><p>You must be young.</p><p>VBScript is indeed less secure than modern scripting languages. This is because once enabled, VBScript can do *anything* it wants to. There is no fine-grained control to say "You can display an alert using VBScript, but you can't update the Registry or replace an executable." It can either do everything, or nothing.</p><p>Newer languages are built with an understanding that certain parts of the language are riskier than others.</p></div>
	</div>

